Version 2.9:
- [!] 26 Oct 2007, Alien - Bug (0028143): Pin codes were generated twice when using an external application. Fixed.
- [+] 5 Sep 2007, Alien - Improvement (0022000): The module is adapted to commercial design schemes.

Version 2.8:
- [+] 22 Jun 2007, Sheriff - Improvement (0022233): EGoods + AOM: the compatibility of these modules has been improved.
- [!] 27 Mar 2007, Sheriff - Bug (0018241): Egoods download links were available even through the related order didn't have the "Processed" status. Fixed.

Version 2.7:
- [!] 09 Sep 2006, Osipov - Bug (0010441): The PINs do not display on the printable version of the order. Fixed.
- [!] 15 Aug 2006, Osipov - Bug (0010080): The 'Download for free' link(s) were not visible in 'modern' skins. Fixed.

Version 2.6:
- [!] 08 Feb 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0005802): After an order's status had been changed from "Q" to "P" for the first time, links to downloadable files were not displayed correctly in the invoice e-mailed to the customer. Fixed.

Version 2.5:
- [!] 19 Oct 2005, Sheriff - Bug: It was possible to add empty PIN codes and zero-length filenames as product files. Fixed.
- [+] 19 Oct 2005, Oley - Improvement: Egoods module reference manual has been rewritten from scratch.
- [+] 18 Oct 2005, Sheriff - Improvement: Code optimization was made.
- [+] 17 Oct 2005, Sheriff - Improvoments: User interface improvements in several module's screens, including 'Egoods', 'PIN codes' and 'Import PIN codes' tabs.
- [!] 04 Oct 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0004347): Occasional display of delivery methods for egoods orders occured (improper behavior). Fixed.
- [!] 05 Sep 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0003988): Inconsistensies related to shipping methods and shipping calculations have been fixed.

Version 2.4:
- [!] 04 Aug 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0003713): Problem (SQL query related) with PIN-code deallocation when declining/marking orders as failed is fixed.

Version 2.3:
- [+] 08 Jun 2005, Asd - Improvement: The product cannot be sold if there are no PIN-codes available.
- [+] 08 Jun 2005, Asd - Improvement: A new functionality is implemented to allow the store administrator to be notified when amount of available PIN-codes reaches the low limit.
- [+] 07 Jun 2005, Asd - Improvement: Pin-code is now tied to the name of the product and the category where it belongs to (it used to be tied to product_id).
- [+] 06 Jun 2005, Asd - Improvement: The service fields 'item_id' and 'order_id' have been removed from the list of importable fields to avoid the confusion about the purpose of these fields.
- [!] 07 Mar 2005, Asd - Bug: The compiled code/templates cache was not cleaned up during the module uninstallation. Fixed.

Version 2.2:

 - [!] 02 Mar 2005, Asd - Bug: The incorrect paths to the module part caused incompatibility between the module and LiteCommerce ASP. Fixed.
 - [!] 10 Jan 2005, Sheriff - Bug: The misspelling in the "Access denied" phrase. Fixed.

Version 2.1:

 - Fixed a bug regarding freeing pin codes when an order is failed.
 - Fixed a bug regarding sending pin codes when an order is placed using a web-based payment method.
 - It is possible to free pin codes manually now.
 - Values in "Manually generated download links:" are now inherited from the global module configuration.

